"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-france-airport-strike-paris-olympics-worker-unions-cgt-cfdt-fo-unsa-b1169456.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|World  Four unions representing workers atairportsin Paris have called for astrikethe week before the Summer Olympics in a dispute over bonuses for staff.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.657677787140375e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The CGT, CFDT, FO and UNSA unions announced they would file a strike motion for July 17 - nine days before the first day of the Games.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4532380054525926e-17, \"text\": \"CGT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\"}, {\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CFDT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q178790\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Democratic_Confederation_of_Labour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The unions have demanded that staff receive an Olympic bonus at A\\u00e9roports de Paris (ADP), the state-owned firm which operates bothCharles de Gaulle/Roissy and Orly airports.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 590, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groupe_ADP\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9296515971550817e-21, \"text\": \"A\\u00e9roports de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groupe_ADP\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groupe_ADP\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement on Monday, they denounced \\\"unilateral decisions from the chief executive to pay a bonus to only some personnel\\\".\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The scale of the potential disruption to travel was not immediately clear.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both airports will serve as the main gateway for tourists to enter France for the Games, which begin on July 26.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999992247870344, \"rank\": 6.081507060160283e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up to 350,000 people are expected to transit through both airports during the Olympics, according toLe Monde.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thousands of athletes will begin arriving in the Olympic Village from July 18.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999918813955, \"rank\": 8.118362630325537e-09, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unions representing workers across the public sector in France have demanded increased pay for having to work through the Games, which last until August 11.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999992247870344, \"rank\": 6.081507060160283e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pay demands have been made by police, air traffic controllers, rubbish collectors, central government employees and train drivers.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes a day afterthe leftist New Popular Front (NFP) unexpectedly secured the highest number of seatsin a snap election called by PresidentEmmanuel Macron.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.980685141111489e-16, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The result was a major setback for forMarine Le Pen's far right National Rally (RN), which opinion polls had predicted would win the second-round ballot but ended up in the third spot.\", \"from\":